Detomidine HCl produce dose-dependent sedative and analgesic effects, mediatated by activation of α2 catecholamine receptors.

Gefitinib (ZD-1839) is an EGFR inhibitor for Tyr1173, Tyr992, Tyr1173 and Tyr992 in the NR6wtEGFR and NR6W cells with IC50 of 37 nM, 37nM, 26 nM and 57 nM, respectively.

Bromfenac Sodium is a nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drug (NSAID), which has anti-inflammatory activity and may block prostaglandin synthesis by inhibiting cyclooxygenase 1 and 2.

Hygromycin B, a selective antibiotic that is effective on most bacteria, fungi and higher eukaryotes, inhibits protein synthesis by interfering with translocation and causing mistranslation at the 70S ribosome.

Reboxetine is a norepinephrine reuptake inhibitor with Ki of 8.2 nM.

Vardenafil HCl Trihydrate is a new type PDE inhibitor with IC50 of 0.7 and 180 nM for PDE5 and PDE1, respectively.
Amphotericin B (AmB) is an amphipathic polyene antibiotic which permeabilizes ergosterol-containing membranes.

Oxiglutatione is the oxidized disulfide form of glutathione (GSH) with potential protective activity.

Leflunomide is a pyrimidine synthesis inhibitor belonging to the DMARD, used as an immunosuppressant agent.

Flurbiprofen is a member of the phenylalkanoic acid derivative family of non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drugs (NSAIDs).

Salirasib is a potent competitive prenylated protein methyltransferase (PPMTase) inhibitor with Ki of 2.6 μM, which inhibits Ras methylation. Phase 2.
Carvedilol is a non-selective beta blocker/alpha-1 blocker, used to treat congestive heart failure (CHF) and high blood pressure.
Clotrimazole alters the permeability of the fungal cell wall by inhibiting the biosynthesis of ergosterol, used in the treatment of fungal infections.
Prilocaine is a local anesthetic of the amino amide type. It acts on sodium channels on the neuronal cell membrane, limiting the spread of seizure activity and reducing seizure propagation.
Abexinostat (PCI-24781) is a novel pan-HDAC inhibitor mostly targeting HDAC1 with Ki of 7 nM, modest potent to HDACs 2, 3, 6, and 10 and greater than 40-fold selectivity against HDAC8. Phase 1/2.
Desogestrel is a synthetic progestational hormone used often as the progestogenic component of combined oral contraceptive agents.
Afloqualone (AFQ) is a quinazolinone family GABAergic drug with muscle-relaxant and sedative effects, showing the agonist activity at the β subtype of the GABAa receptor.

Mercaptopurine is a widely used antileukemic agent and immunosuppressive drug that inhibits de novo purine synthesis through incorporation of thiopurine methyltransferase metabolites into DNA and RNA.
Isoprenaline is a non-selective beta-adrenergic receptor agonist, used for the treatment of bradycardia and heart block.

Miltefosine inhibits PI3K/Akt activity with ED50 of 17.2 μM and 8.1 μM in carcinoma cell lines A431 and HeLa, first oral drug for Visceral leishmaniasis, effective against both promastigotes and amastigotes.
Tiagabine Hydrochloride is the hydrochloride salt form of tiagabine, a nipecotic acid derivative with anticonvulsant property. A selective gamma-aminobutyric acid (GABA) reuptake inhibitor.
Sodium butyrate, sodium salt of butyric acid, is a histone deacetylase inhibitor and competitively binds to the zinc sites of class I and II histone deacetylases (HDACs).
Sodium salicylate is used in medicine as an analgesic and antipyretic.
Betamipron is a chemical compound which is used together with panipenem to inhibit panipenem uptake into the renal tubule and prevent nephrotoxicity.
Tobramycin is an aminoglycoside antibiotic with an IC50 of 9.7 μM.

i-Inositol, also known as myo-inositol, is a chemical compound which is sugar alcohol. i-Inositol is involved in a number of biological processes including insulin signal transduction, cytoskeleton transduction and so on.
Topiroxostat is a xanthine oxidoreductase (XOR) inhibitor and used for treatment of gout and hyperuricemia.
Teriflunomide is the active metabolite of leflunomide, inhibiting pyrimidine de novo synthesis by blocking the enzyme dihydroorotate dehydrogenase, used as an immunomodulatory agent.
Saracatinib (AZD0530) is a potent Src inhibitor with IC50 of 2.7 nM in cell-free assays, and potent to c-Yes, Fyn, Lyn, Blk, Fgr and Lck less active for Abl and EGFR (L858R and L861Q). Phase 2/3.
Chlorocresol is an activator of ryanodine receptor.
Acipimox is a niacin derivative used as a hypolipidemic agent.
Docusate Sodium is a laxative used to treat constipation, for constipation due to the use of opiates it maybe used with a stimulant laxative, can be taken by mouth or rectally.
Bortezomib (PS-341) is a potent 20S proteasome inhibitor with Ki of 0.6 nM. It exhibits favorable selectivity towards tumor cells over normal cells.
Benzethonium chloride is a potent inhibitor of nAChRs, it inhibits α4β2 nAChRs and α7 nAChRs with IC50 of 49 nM and 122 nM, respectively.
Prucalopride is a selective, high affinity 5-HT4 receptor agonist. The Ki values of prucalopride for human 5-HT(4a) and 5-HT(4b) receptor are 2.5 nM and 8 nM, respectively.
Laquinimod is a potent immunomodulator. Phase 3.
Micafungin Sodium is an inhibitor of 1, 3-beta-D-glucan synthesis, used as an antifungal drug.
Fimasartan is a non-peptide angiotensin II receptor antagonist (ARB) with noncompetitive, insurmountable binding with the AT1 receptor. It is used for the treatment of hypertension and heart failure.
Grazoprevir anhydrous is a Hepatitis C Virus NS3/4A Protease inhibitor with IC50 values of 7pM, 4pM, and 62pM for HCV genotype 1a, 1B, and 4 respectively.
Repaglinide is a potassium channel blocker, which lowers blood glucose by stimulating the release of insulin from the pancreas, used the treatment of type II diabetes.
Vonoprazan Fumarate (TAK-438) is a novel P-CAB (potassium-competitive acid blocker) that reversibly inhibits H+/K+, ATPase with IC50 of 19 nM (pH 6.5), controls gastric acid secretion. Phase 3.
Trospium chloride  is a competitive muscarinic cholinergic receptor antagonist.

L-cysteine Hydrochloride, also known as L-CYSTEINE or Cysteine HCL (anhydrous), is classified as a cysteine or a cysteine derivative that increases glutathione levels and is important for lung and brain function and liver detoxification.
Isosorbide is a heterocyclic compound that is derived from glucose, used as a diuretic.
Telaprevir (VX-950) is an HCV NS3-4A serine protease inhibitor with IC50 of 0.35 μM.
Sitagliptin is an oral and highly selective DPP-4 inhibitor with an IC50 of 18 nM. It is used for the treatment of type 2 diabetes.

Lisinopril is an angiotensin-converting enzyme (ACE) inhibitor, used in treatment of hypertension, congestive heart failure, and heart attacks, and also in preventing renal and retinal complications of diabetes.
Meprednisone is a glucocorticoid and a methylated derivative of prednisone.
Moxonidine is a selective agonist at the imidazoline receptor subtype 1, used as antihypertensive agent.
Miconazole Nitrate is an imidazole antifungal agent by inhibiting ergosterol biosynthesis and inducing ROS, used to treat vaginal yeast infections.
Guaifenesin is an expectorant used to relieve chest congestion.
Sodium Nitroprusside  Dihydrate is a potent vasodilator working through releasing NO spontaneously in blood.
Manidipine 2HCl is a HCl salt form of Manidipine, which is a calcium channel blocker with IC50 of 2.6 nM, used clinically as an antihypertensive. Phase 4.
Lumefantrine is an antimalarial agent used to treat acute uncomplicated malaria.
Ropivacaine HCl is an anaesthetic agent and blocks impulse conduction in nerve fibres through inhibiting sodium ion influx reversibly.
Plerixafor (AMD3100) is a chemokine receptor antagonist for CXCR4 and CXCL12-mediated chemotaxis with IC50 of 44 nM and 5.7 nM in cell-free assays, respectively.

Prucalopride is a selective, high affinity 5-HT receptor agonist for 5-HT4A and 5-HT4B receptor with Ki of 2.5 nM and 8 nM, respectively, exhibits >290-fold selectivity against other 5-HT receptor subtypes.
Eslicarbazepine acetate is an antiepileptic drug.

Etretinate is an oral aromatic retinoid acid which is effective in psoriasis and other dermatological syndromes. It activates retinoid receptors, causing an induction of cell differentiation, inhibition of cell proliferation, and inhibition of tissue infiltration by inflammatory cells.
Niflumic acid is an inhibitor of cyclooxygenase-2 used for joint and muscular pain.
Idasanutlin (RG-7388) is a potent and selective p53-MDM2 inhibitor with IC50 of 6 nM showing improved in vitro binding as well as cellular potency/selectivity.
Ranitidine is a histamine H2-receptor antagonist, used to treat stomach or intestinal ulcers.
Nystatin, which belongs to the polyene group of antimycotics, is frequently used as a topical agent in the treatment of oro-pharyngeal candidosis.
Luliconazole is a broad-spectrum antifungal drug.
Sitagliptin phosphate monohydrate is a potent inhibitor of DPP-IV with IC50 of 19 nM in Caco-2 cell extracts.
Etofibrate is a combination of clofibrate and niacin, used to treat hyperlipemia.
Toremifene Citrate is an oral selective estrogen receptor modulator (SERM), used in the treatment of advanced breast cancer.
Efavirenz is a synthetic non-nucleoside reverse transcriptase (RT) inhibitor with antiviral activity.
Bilastine is a new, well-tolerated, nonsedating H1 receptor antihistamine and has a rapid onset and prolonged duration of action.
Colistin is a cyclic cationic decapeptide linked to a fatty acid side chain, it belongs to a group of similarly structured bacterial antimicrobial peptides.
Noradrenaline bitartrate monohydrate is a direct alpha-adrenergic receptors stimulator.
Bismuth Subcitrate is an antibiotic used to treat stomach ulcers associated with Helicobacter pylori, a bacterial infection.
Darunavir Ethanolate (DRV) is a nonpeptidic HIV protease inhibitor, used to treat HIV infection.
Nafamostat mesilate is a synthetic serine protease inhibitor, used as an anticoagulant during hemodialysis.
Dexmedetomidine HCl is a highly selective and potent alpha-2 adrenoceptor agonist, which reduces anesthetic requirements for patients by providing significant sedation.
Folic acid, a B vitamin, plays an important role in cell division and in the synthesis of amino acids and nucleic acids like DNA.
Flumethasone is a glucocorticoid receptor agonist, this complex binds to the nucleus causing a variety of genetic activation and repressions.

Selexipag is an orally active, first-in-class, selective prostacyclin IP receptor agonist with Ki value of 260 nM for human IP, whereas Ki values > 10,000 nM are measured at the other human G-protein-coupled prostanoid receptors (EP1-4, DP, FP and TP).
Ronidazole is an antiprotozoal agent.
Nelarabine is a purine nucleoside analog and DNA synthesis inhibitor with IC50 from 0.067-2.15 μM in tumor cells.
Dopamine HCl is a catecholamine neurotransmitter present in a wide variety of animals,And a dopamine D1-5 receptors agonist.
Azelastine HCl is a potent, second-generation, selective, histamine receptor antagonist, used in the treatment of rhinitis.
Ledipasvir (GS5885) is a HCV NS5A polymerase inhibitor, used for the treatment of hepatitis C virus infection.
Phenformin HCl is a hydrochloride salt of phenformin that is an anti-diabetic drug from the biguanide class. It activates AMPK, increasing activity and phosphorylation.
Pefloxacin Mesylate is a synthetic chemotherapeutic agent and an antibacterial agent with IC50 of 6.7 nM.

6-Mercaptopurine Monohydrate is a widely used antileukemic agent and immunosuppressive drug that inhibits de novo purine synthesis through incorporation of thiopurine methyltransferase metabolites into DNA and RNA.
Nimesulide is a relatively COX-2 selective inhibitor with IC50 of 26 μM.
Tepotinib (EMD 1214063) is a potent and selective c-Met inhibitor with IC50 of 4 nM, >200-fold selective for c-Met than IRAK4, TrkA, Axl, IRAK1, and Mer. Phase 1.
Cangrelor is a potent, competitive P2Y12 receptor inhibitor that is administered by intravenous infusion and rapidly achieves near complete inhibition of ADP-induced platelet aggregation.
Cinchophen is an analgesic drug that is frequently used to treat gout.
Trimethoprim is a bacteriostatic antibiotic mainly used in the prophylaxis and treatment of urinary tract infections.
Inosine is a nucleoside that is formed when hypoxanthine is attached to a ribose ring via a &beta-N9-glycosidic bond.
Pramoxine is a topical local anesthetic that has been shown to have antipruritic properties.

Alcaftadine is a high affinity ligand for the H1 receptor, with a pKi (8.5) that is comparable with that of other H1 antihistamines. Alcaftadine is also an antagonist for H2 and H4 receptors with no affinity for the H3 receptor.
Crystal violet is a triarylmethane dye.
Mesalamine is a specific inhibitor of TNFα-induced IKK activity, used to treat inflammatory bowel disease.

Triamcinolone is a glucocorticoid given, as the free alcohol or in esterified form, orally, intramuscularly, by local injection, by inhalation, or applied topically in the management of various disorders in which corticosteroids are indicated.
Entrectinib (RXDX-101) is an orally bioavailable pan-TrkA/B/C, ROS1 and ALK inhibitor with IC50 ranging between 0.1 and 1.7 nM. Phase 2.
Pregnenolone is an endogenous steroid hormone, used in the treatment of fatigue, Alzheimer’s disease, trauma and injuries.
Ifosfamide is a nitrogen mustard alkylating agent used in the treatment of cancer.
Azilsartan is an angiotensin II type 1 (AT1) receptor antagonist with IC50 of 2.6 nM.
Terbinafine HCl inhibits ergosterol synthesis by inhibiting squalene epoxidase, used as an antifungal drug.
Pomalidomide inhibits LPS-induced TNF-α release with IC50 of 13 nM in PBMCs.
Antipyrine is an analgesic and antipyretic agent selective COX-3 inhibitor.
Pioglitazone HCl is a selective peroxisome proliferator-activated receptor-gamma (PPARgamma) agonist, used to treat diabetes.
Propofol (Diprivan) is a short-acting, intravenously administered hypnotic agent.
Atenolol is a selective β1 receptor antagonist with log Kd values of ?6.66±0.05, ?5.99±0.14, ?4.11±0.07 for binding to the human β1-, β2- and β3-adrenoceptors.
Tenofovir Alafenamide (GS-7340) is a prodrug of tenofovir, which is a reverse transcriptase inhibitor, used to treat HIV and Hepatitis B.

Anastrozole is a third-generation nonsteroidal selective aromatase inhibitor. It may offer greater selectivity compared with other aromatase inhibitors, being without any intrinsic endocrine effects and with no apparent effect on the synthesis of adrenal steroids.
Sildenafil Mesylate is a mesylate form of Sildenafil, an inhibitor of Phosphodiesterase 5.
Imiquimod is a novel synthetic agent with immune response modifying activity.
Tolnaftate is a synthetic thiocarbamate used as an anti-fungal agent.

Thioguanine, a purine antimetabolite, inhibits DNMT1 activity through ubiquitin-targeted degradation, used in the treatment of acute lymphoblastic leukemia, autoimmune disorders (e.g., Crohn's disease, rheumatoid arthritis) and organ transplant recipients.
Ibuprofen Lysine is a non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drug.
Acetazolamide, a potent carbonic anhydrase (CA) inhibitor, is commonly used in clinical practice as an immediate and readily available option for acute reduction of intraocular pressure(IOP).
Silodosin is a highly selective α1A-adrenoceptor antagonist, used in treatment of benign prostatic hyperplasia.
(S)-crizotinib, the (S)-enantiomer of crizotinib, is a potent MTH1 (NUDT1) inhibitor with IC50 of 72 nM in a cell-free assay.
Streptomycin sulfate is a sulfate salt of streptomycin that is a protein synthesis inhibitor.
Imipenem acts as an inhibitor of AmpC β-lactamase and is an antibiotic useful for the treatment of a number of bacterial infections.
Ketorolac (Ketorolac tromethamine) is a non-selective COX inhibitor of COX-1 and COX-2 with IC50 of 1.23 μM and 3.50 μM, respectively.
Indacaterol is an ultra-long-acting β-adrenoceptor agonist with pKi of 7.36 for β1-adrenoceptor and pKi of 5.48 for β2-adrenoceptor.
Primaquine Diphosphate is a transmission-blocking anti-malarial clinically available, displaying a marked activity against gametocytes of all species of human malaria.
Xylometazoline is an α-adrenoceptor agonist commonly used as nasal decongestant, exhibits highest potency at α2B-adrenoceptor subtype with EC50 of 99 μM.
Aciclovir is a synthetic nucleoside analogue active against herpesviruses.
Nilutamide is a nonsteroidal antiandrogen (NSAA) with affinity for androgen receptors (but not for progestogen, estrogen, or glucocorticoid receptors). It is used in the treatment of prostate cancer.
Chlorpropamide is a sulfonylurea class drug for type 2 diabetes mellitus.
Veliparib (ABT-888) is a potent inhibitor of PARP1 and PARP2 with Ki of 5.2 nM and 2.9 nM in cell-free assays, respectively. It is inactive to SIRT2. Phase 3.

Trometamol is a proton acceptor used to treat acidemia. It inhibits both isoforms of cyclooxygenases (COX1 and COX2), thereby blocking the conversion of arachidonic acid to pro-inflammatory pro-prostaglandins.
Iniparib (BSI-201) is a PARP1 inhibitor with demonstrated effectiveness in triple-negative breast cancer (TNBC). Phase 3.
Mupirocin is an isoleucyl t-RNA synthetase inhibitor, used in the treatment of bacterial skin infections.
Mometasone Furoate is a glucocorticoid receptor agonist, used topically to reduce inflammation of the skin or in the airways.

Vitamin E Acetate is the stable form of Vitamin E most often used in cosmetic formulations for its skin care benefits. It protects the cells against free radicals and prevents the peroxidation of body fats as an in-vivo antioxidant.
Potassium acetate is the potassium salt of acetic acid, which is a synthetic carboxylic acid with antibacterial and antifungal properties.
Pyrantel pamoate, a broad-spectrum anthelmintic drug, is used to treat a number of parasitic worm infections.
Clopidol is an antiprotozoal agent.

Retigabine(free base) is a novel anticonvulsant with activity in a broad range of seizure models. The mechanism of action involves opening of neuronal K(V)7.2-7.5 (formerly KCNQ2-5) voltage-activated K(+) channels.
Amlodipine is a long-acting calcium channel blocker, used to lower blood pressure and prevent chest pain.
Alizapride HCl is a dopamine receptor antagonist used for the theropy of nausea and vomiting.
Chlorhexidine hydrochloride is an antiseptic effective against a wide variety of gram-negative and gram-positive organisms.
Levosulpiride is a selective antagonist for D2 dopamine receptors used as an antipsychotic and prokinetic agent.
Cyclizine 2HCl is a piperazine derivative with Histamine H1 receptor antagonist activity.
Amprolium chloride is a thiamin antagonist, which prevents carbohydrate synthesis by blocking thiamine uptake.

Flavopiridol (Alvocidib) competes with ATP to inhibit CDKs including CDK1, CDK2, CDK4, CDK6, and CDK9 with IC50 values in the 20-100 nM range. It is more selective for CDK1, 2, 4, 6, 9 versus CDK7. Flavopiridol is initially found to inhibit EGFR and PKA. Phase 1/2.
Nedaplatin is a derivative of cisplatin and DNA damage agent for tumor colony forming units with IC50 of 94 μM.
Selinexor (KPT-330) is an orally bioavailable selective CRM1 inhibitor. Phase 2.
Zonisamide is a voltage-dependent sodium channel and T-type calcium channel blocker, used as an antiepileptic drug.

Carfilzomib (PR-171) is an irreversible proteasome inhibitor with IC50 of <5 nM in ANBL-6 cells, displayed preferential in vitro inhibitory potency against the ChT-L activity in the β5 subunit, but little or no effect on the PGPH and T-L activities.

Duvelisib (IPI-145, INK1197) is a novel and selective PI3K δ/γ inhibitor with Ki and IC50 of 23 pM/243 pM and 1 nM/50 nM in cell-free assays, highly selective for PI3K δ/γ than other protein kinases. Phase 3.
Rotigotine is a dopamine receptor agonist, used in the treatment of Parkinson's disease and restless legs syndrome.
Pargyline is an irreversible inhibitor of monoamine oxidase (MAO)-B with Ki values of 13 and 0.5 μM for time-dependent inhibition of the activity of MAO-A and -B, respectivey.
Nimodipine is a dihydropyridine calcium channel blocker and an autophagy inhibitor, used in the treatment of high blood pressure.
DL-panthenol is a racemic mixture of D and L form of panthenol,a provitamin of B5.
Acemetacin is a non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drug and a glycolic acid ester of indometacin that is a cyclooxygenase inhibitor.
Sodium Carbonate is the disodium salt of carbonic acid with alkalinizing property.
Prednisolone Acetate is a synthetic corticosteroid drug that is particularly effective as an immunosuppressant agent.
Lomitapide is a potent microsomal triglyceride transfer protein (MTP) inhibitor, used in the treatment of familial hypercholesterolemia.
Gallic acid, known as powerful antioxidants, is an organic acid found in a variety of foods and herbs.
Amuvatinib (MP-470) is a potent and multi-targeted inhibitor of c-Kit, PDGFRα and Flt3 with IC50 of 10 nM, 40 nM and 81 nM, respectively. Phase 2.
Buspirone is a serotonergic (5HT(1A) receptor agonist) anxiolytic drug with some D(2) dopaminergic effect, used for anxiety disorders.

Valaciclovir HCl, an aciclovir prodrug, inhibits activity of virus DNA polymerase, used to treat infections caused by herpes simplex virus (HSV) and varicella zoster virus, and for prophylaxis against cytomegalovirus (CMV).
Trimebutine is an agonist of peripheral mu, kappa and delta opiate receptors, used as spasmolytic agent for treatment of both acute and chronic abdominal pain.
Sulfapyridine  is a sulfonamide antibacterial.
Fingolimod (FTY720) HCl is a S1P antagonist with IC50 of 0.033 nM in K562, and NK cells.
Roflumilast is a selective inhibitor of PDE4 with IC50 of 0.2-4.3 nM in a cell-free assay.
Argatroban is a direct, selective thrombin inhibitor with anticoagulant effects.
Dimethadione is an anticonvulsant that is the active metabolite of trimethadione.
Paromomycin Sulfate is an aminoglycoside antibiotics inhibiting protein synthesis in non-resistant cells by binding to 16S ribosomal RNA.
Oxaliplatin inhibits DNA synthesis by conforming DNA adducts in RT4, TCCSUP, A2780, HT-29, U-373MG, U-87MG, SK-MEL-2, and HT-144 cells.
Cefoperazone is a cephalosporin antibiotic for inhibition of rMrp2-mediated [3H]E217βG uptake with IC50 of 199 μM.
Fenofibric acid is a fibrate that acts as a lipid-lowering agent, decreasing low-density lipoprotein cholesterol and triglycerides.
Sulfamethazine is a sulfonamide antibacterial.
Doxofylline is a phosphodiesterase inhibitor and a xanthine derivative drug for asthma.
Chlorotrianisene is a synthetic, non-steroidal estrogen. It is a selective estrogen receptor modulator.
Napabucasin is an orally available Stat3 and cancer cell stemness inhibitor.
Ramosetron Hydrochloride is the hydrochloride salt of ramosetron, a selective serotonin (5-HT) receptor antagonist with potential antiemetic activity.

Avagacestat (BMS-708163) is a potent, selective, orally bioavailable γ-secretase inhibitor of Aβ40 and Aβ42 with IC50 of 0.3 nM and 0.27 nM, demonstrating a 193-fold selectivity against Notch. Phase 2.
Paliperidone, the main active metabolite of Risperidone, is a potent serotonin-2A and dopamine-2 receptor antagonist, used in the treatment of schizophrenia.
Ketanserin is a specific 5-HT2A serotonin receptor antagonist with Ki of 2.5 nM for rat and human 5-HT2A, used as an antihypertensive drug.
Brivaracetam is a racetam derivative with anticonvulsant properties, usually used in the treatment of partial-onset seizures.
Ceftiofur HCl is a cephalosporin antibiotic, used to treat both Gram-positive and Gram-negative bacteria infection.

Tadalafil is a PDE-5 inhibitor with IC50 of 1.8 nM in a cell-free assay. Tadalafil is at least 9000 times more selective for PDE5 than most of the other families of PDEs, with the exception of PDE11. It can partial inhibits PDE11

Dovitinib (TKI258, CHIR258) is a multitargeted RTK inhibitor, mostly for class III (FLT3/c-Kit) with IC50 of 1 nM/2 nM, also potent to class IV (FGFR1/3) and class V (VEGFR1-4) RTKs with IC50 of 8-13 nM, less potent to InsR, EGFR, c-Met, EphA2, Tie2, IGF-1R and HER2 in cell-free assays. Phase 4.
Dasatinib Monohydrate is a novel, potent and multi-targeted inhibitor that targets Abl, Src and c-Kit, with IC50 of <1 nM, 0.8 nM and 79 nM, respectively.
Danofloxacin is a fluoroquinolone antibacterial for veterinary use, with MIC90 of 0.28 μM.

Hydroxyprogesterone Caproate is a synthetic progestational agent. It binds to and activates nuclear progesterone receptors in the reproductive system and inhibits ovulation and an alteration in the cervical mucus and endometrium.

Danthron is an organic substance. It used to be a laxatica and now is currently used as an antioxidant in synthetic lubricants, in the synthesis of experimental antitumor agents, as a fungicide and as an intermediate for making dyes.
Cyclosporin A is an immunosuppressive agent, binds to the cyclophilin and then inhibits calcineurin with IC50 of 7 nM in a cell-free assay, widely used in organ transplantation to prevent rejection.

Cephalothin is a semisynthetic, beta-lactam, first-generation cephalosporin antibiotic with bactericidal activity. Cephalothin binds to and inactivates penicillin-binding proteins (PBP) located on the inner membrane of the bacterial cell wall.
Galanthamine is an AChE inhibitor with IC50 of 0.35 μM, exhibits 50-fold selectivity against butyryl-cholinesterase.
Prednisolone is a synthetic glucocorticoid with anti-inflammatory and immunomodulating properties.
Tedizolid is an oxazolidinone-class antibiotic. Tedizolid phosphate is a phosphate ester prodrug of the active compound tedizolid.

Cabozantinib malate (XL184) is the malate of Cabozantinib, a potent VEGFR2 inhibitor with IC50 of 0.035 nM and also inhibits c-Met, Ret, Kit, Flt-1/3/4, Tie2, and AXL with IC50 of 1.3 nM, 4 nM, 4.6 nM, 12 nM/11.3 nM/6 nM, 14.3 nM and 7 nM in cell-free assays, respectively.
Doxapram HCl inhibits TASK-1, TASK-3, TASK-1/TASK-3 heterodimeric channel function with EC50 of 410 nM, 37 μM, 9 μM, respectively.
Lercanidipine is a calcium channel blocker of the dihydropyridine class.
Nizatidine is a histamine H2 receptor antagonist with IC50 of 0.9 nM, also inhibits AChE with IC50 of 6.7 μM.
Chlormadinone acetate is a steroidal progestin with additional antiandrogen and antigonadotropic effects, used often in combinations as an oral contraceptive. Its half-life is about 34-38 hours.
Afuresertib (GSK2110183) is a potent, orally bioavailable Akt inhibitor with Ki of 0.08 nM, 2 nM, and 2.6 nM for Akt1, Akt2, and Akt3, respectively. Phase 2.
Ibuprofen (Dolgesic) is an anti-inflammatory inhibitor targeting COX-1 and COX-2 with IC50 of 13 μM and 370 μM, respectively.
Telbivudine is a potent, and selective HBV reverse transcriptase inhibitor, used to treat HBV infection.
Ciprofibrate is a peroxisome proliferator-activated receptor agonist.
Vitamin C is a water-soluble vitamin indicated for the prevention and treatment of scurvy.
Lenalidomide (CC-5013) is a TNF-α secretion inhibitor with IC50 of 13 nM in PBMCs.
Brinzolamide is a potent carbonic anhydrase II inhibitor with IC50 of 3.19 nM.
Galeterone is a selective CYP17 inhibitor and androgen receptor (AR) antagonist with IC50 of 300 nM and 384 nM, respectively, and is a potent inhibitor of human prostate tumor growth. Phase 2.

Hydroquinone is a Melanin Synthesis Inhibitor. The physiologic effect of hydroquinone is by means of Depigmenting Activity. It also posesses antioxidant properties that can cause toxicity in several organs, notably the kidney.
Dehydrocholic acid is a semisynthetic bile acid made from cholic acid. It is used as a cholagogue, hydrocholeretic, diuretic, and as a diagnostic aid.
Ivabradine HCl, a new If inhibitor with IC 50 of 2.9 μM which acts specifically on the pacemaker activity of the sinoatrial node, is a pure heart rate lowering agent.
Voxtalisib (SAR245409, XL765) Analogue is a dual inhibitor of mTOR/PI3K, mostly for p110γ with IC50 of 9 nM also inhibits DNA-PK and mTOR. Phase 1/2.

Epacadostat (INCB024360) is a potent and selective indoleamine 2,3-dioxygenase (IDO1) inhibitor with IC50 of 10 nM and displays high selectivity over other related enzymes such as IDO2 or tryptophan 2,3-dioxygenase (TDO).
Parecoxib is a selective COX2 inhibitor.
Chlortetracycline HCl is the first identified tetracycline antibiotic.
Lapatinib (GW-572016) Ditosylate is a potent EGFR and ErbB2 inhibitor with IC50 of 10.8 and 9.2 nM in cell-free assays, respectively.
Doxepin is a tricyclic antidepressant formulated as a mixture of E-(trans) and Z-(cis) stereoisomers. It inhibits CYP2D6 activity in vivo.
Nicardipine is a dihydropyridine calcium-channel blocking agent used for the treatment of vascular disorders.
Sulfathiazole is an organosulfur compound that has been used as a short-acting sulfa drug.
Resminostat dose-dependently and selectively inhibits HDAC1/3/6 with IC50 of 42.5 nM/50.1 nM/71.8 nM, less potent to HDAC8 with IC50 of 877 nM.
Istradefylline is a selective adenosine A2A receptor (A2AR) antagonist with Ki of 2.2 nM. Phase 3.
Risedronate Sodium, a nitrogen-containing bisphosphonate, inhibits osteoclast-mediated bone resorption and modulates bone metabolism, used in the treatment of osteoporosis.
D-Mannitol is an osmotic diuretic agent and a weak renal vasodilator.
Nadifloxacin is a topical fluoroquinolone antibiotic for the treatment of acne vulgaris.
Amikacin sulfate binds to 16S rRNA (bacterial 30S ribosome), causing misreading of mRNA and supressing proteins synthesis.
Zalcitabine is a nucleoside analog HIV reverse transcriptase inhibitor (NARTI).

Cediranib (AZD2171) is a highly potent VEGFR(KDR) inhibitor with IC50 of <1 nM, also inhibits Flt1/4 with IC50 of 5 nM/≤3 nM, similar activity against c-Kit and PDGFRβ, 36-, 110-fold and >1000-fold selective more for VEGFR than PDGFR-α, CSF-1R and Flt3 in HUVEC cells. Phase 3.
Enalaprilat is an angiotensin-converting enzyme (ACE) inhibitor with IC50 of 1.94 nM.
Mecarbinate is a chemical intermediate of arbidol hydrochloride.
Octocrylene is an organic compound used as an ingredient in sunscreens and cosmetics.
Delamanid is a new anti-tuberculosis drug with an excellent intracellular bactericidal activity and a high accumulation rate.
Hexamethonium?Dibromide is a selective antagonist of neuronal-type nicotinic AChR in ganglia.

Entospletinib (GS-9973) is an orally bioavailable, selective Syk inhibitor with IC50 of 7.7 nM in a cell-free assay and showed 13- to >1000-fold cellular selectivity for Syk over other kinases(including Jak2, ckit, Flt3, Ret, KDR) as assessed by target protein phosphorylation or functional response.
Taladegib (LY2940680) binds to the Smoothened (Smo) receptor and potently inhibits Hedgehog (Hh) signaling. Phase 1/2.
Pyridoxine, also known as vitamin B6, is a form of vitamin B6 found commonly in food and used as dietary supplement. It is a cofactor for both glutamic acid decarboxylase and GABA transaminase.

Molsidomine is an orally active, long acting vasodilating drug. Molsidomine is metabolized in the liver to the active metabolite linsidomine. Linsidomine is an unstable compound that releases nitric oxide (NO) upon decay as the actual vasodilating compound.

Procaine is a benzoic acid derivative with local anesthetic and antiarrhythmic properties. Procaine binds to and inhibits voltage-gated sodium channels, thereby inhibiting the ionic flux required for the initiation and conduction of impulses.
Propiverine is an anticholinergic drug used for the treatment of overactive bladder and urinary incontinence.
Avanafil is a highly selective PDE5 inhibitor with IC50 of 5.2 nM, >121-fold selectivity over other PDEs.
Ketotifen Fumarate is a fumaric acid salt of ketotifen which is a H1-antihistamine and mast cell stabilizer.
Sorafenib Tosylate is a multikinase inhibitor of Raf-1, B-Raf and VEGFR-2 with IC50 of 6 nM, 22 nM and 90 nM in cell-free assays, respectively.
Prazosin HCl is a competitive alpha-1 adrenoceptor antagonist, used to treat high blood pressure or benign prostatic hyperplasia.

Quizartinib (AC220) is a second-generation FLT3 inhibitor for Flt3(ITD/WT) with IC50 of 1.1 nM/4.2 nM in MV4-11 and RS411 cells, respectively, 10-fold more selective for Flt3 than KIT, PDGFRα, PDGFRβ, RET, and CSF-1R. Phase 3.

Oxybuprocaine HCl is a local anesthetic, which is used especially in ophthalmology and otolaryngology.  Oxybuprocaine binds to sodium channel and reversibly stabilizes the neuronal membrane which decreases its permeability to sodium ions
Zibotentan (ZD4054) is a specific Endothelin (ET)A antagonist with IC50 of 21 nM, exhibiting no activity at ETB. Phase 3.

Latanoprost is a prostaglandin F2alpha analogue and a prostanoid selective FP receptor agonist with an ocular hypertensive effect. Latanoprost increases uveoscleral outflow and thereby reduces intraocular pressure.
Isoniazid is a prodrug that blocks the action of fatty acid synthase by interacting with KatG , used for the prevention and treatment of tuberculosis.
Betamethasone Valerate is a moderately potent glucocorticoid steroid with anti-inflammatory and immunosuppressive properties.
Pyrimethamine is a dihydrofolate reductase (DHFR) inhibitor, used as an antimalarial drug.
Spectinomycin 2HCl is a new parenteral antibiotic prepared from Streptomyces spectabilis.
Puromycin 2HCl is an aminonucleoside antibiotic, which acts as a protein synthesis inhibitor.
Amantadine HCl is used to treat or prevent infections of the respiratory tract caused by a certain virus.
Sulfamethoxypyridazine is a long-acting sulfonamide for treatment of Dermatitis herpetiformis.
Dihydralazine sulphate is a dihydralazine-l,4-phthalazine derivative and used as an antihypertensive drug.
Teniposide is a chemotherapeutic medication mainly used in the treatment of childhood acute lymphocytic leukemia (ALL).
Piperazine, GABA receptor agonist, is an anthelmintic used in the treatment of the intestinal nematodes Ascaris lumbricoides and Enterobius vermicularis.
Bexarotene is a retinoid specifically selective for retinoid X receptors, used as an oral antineoplastic agent in the treatment of cutaneous T-cell lymphoma.
Zafirlukast is an oral leukotriene receptor antagonist (LTRA), used to prevent asthma symptoms.
Rifaximin is a RNA synthesis inhibitor by binding the β subunit of the bacterial DNA-dependent RNA polymerase, used to treat traveler's diarrhea caused by certain bacteria.
Aminothiazole can be used as a thyroid inhibitor and it has antibacterial activity.
Dantrolene sodium hemiheptahydrate ia a skeletal muscle relaxant that acts by interfering with excitation-contraction coupling in the muscle fiber.
Loratadine is a histamine H1 receptor antagonist, used to treat allergies. Also acts as a selective inhibitor of B(0)AT2 with IC50 of 4 μM.
Estradiol, or more precisely, 17β-estradiol, is a human sex hormone and steroid, and the primary female sex hormone.
Suprofen is a dual COX-1/COX-2 inhibitor, used as a non-steroidal anti-inflammatory analgesic and antipyretic.

Oclacitinib(PF 03394197) is a novel inhibitor of JAK family members with IC50 ranging from 10 to 99 nM and JAK1-dependent cytokines with IC50 ranging from 36 to 249 nM. It does not inhibit a panel of 38 non-JAK kinases.
Clofarabine inhibits the enzymatic activities of ribonucleotide reductase (IC50 = 65 nM) and DNA polymerase.

Roscovitine (Seliciclib, CYC202) is a potent and selective CDK inhibitor for Cdc2, CDK2 and CDK5 with IC50 of 0.65 μM, 0.7 μM and 0.16 μM in cell-free assays. It shows little effect on CDK4/6. Phase 2.
Atorvastatin Calcium is an inhibitor of HMG-CoA reductase used as a cholesterol-lowering medication that blocks the production of cholesterol.
Methylprednisolone is a synthetic glucocorticoid receptor agonist, used to achieve prompt suppression of inflammation.
Carboplatin is a DNA synthesis inhibitor by binding to DNA and interfering with the cell's repair mechanism in A2780, SKOV-3, IGROV-1, and HX62 cells.
Fosinopril Sodium is the ester prodrug of an angiotensin-converting enzyme (ACE) inhibitor, used for the treatment of hypertension and some types of chronic heart failure.
Conivaptan HCl is an orally active, non-peptide, vasopressin V1A and V2 receptor antagonist, used in the treatment of euvolemic and hypervolemic hyponatremia.
4-Aminopyridine (4-AP) is a potent and non-selective inhibitor of voltage gated potassium channels (Kv) with IC50 values of 170 μM and 230 μM for Kv1.1 and Kv1.2 in CHO cells, respectively.
Lomerizine dihydrochloride is a relatively new L- and T-type calcium channel blocker used in the treatment of migraine.
Amisulpride is an atypical antipsychotic used to treat psychosis in schizophrenia and episodes of mania in bipolar disorder.
Trifluridine is an anti-herpesvirus antiviral agent by interacting viral DNA replication, used primarily on the eye.
Belinostat (PXD101) is a novel HDAC inhibitor with IC50 of 27 nM in a cell-free assay, with activity demonstrated in cisplatin-resistant tumors.

Ixazomib Citrate (MLN9708) immediately hydrolyzed to MLN2238, the biologically active form, on exposure to aqueous solutions or plasma. MLN2238 inhibits the chymotrypsin-like proteolytic (β5) site of the 20S proteasome with IC50/Ki of 3.4 nM/0.93 nM in cell-free assays, less potent to β1 and little activity to β2. Phase 3.
Cefonicid sodium is a cephalosporin antibiotic. It interferes with cell wall biosynthesis in bacteria, leading to lysis of the infectious organism.
Trilostane is an inhibitor of 3β-hydroxysteroid dehydrogenase used in the treatment of Cushing’s syndrome.
Praziquantel is an anthelmintic effective against flatworms.
Fosaprepitant is a water-soluble phosphoryl prodrug for Aprepitant which is a NK1 antagonist.
Piperacillin is a semisynthetic, broad-spectrum, ampicillin derived ureidopenicillin antibiotic proposed for pseudomonas infections.
Safinamide Mesylate is mesylate salt of Safinamide, selectively and reversibly inhibits MAO-B with IC50 of 98 nM, exhibits 5918-fold selectivity against MAO-A. Phase 3.
Alisertib (MLN8237) is a selective Aurora A inhibitor with IC50 of 1.2 nM in a cell-free assay. It has >200-fold higher selectivity for Aurora A than Aurora B. Phase 3.
Ticlopidine HCl is an P2 receptor inhibitor against ADP-induced platelet aggregation with IC50 of ~2 μM.
Dicloxacillin is a β-lactamase resistant penicillin similar to oxacillin and it has activity against gram-positive/negative aerobic and anaerobic bacteria.
Sulfamethoxazole is a sulfonamide bacteriostatic antibiotic with an IC50 of 2.7 μM.
Metronidazole, a synthetic antibacterial and antiprotozoal agent of the nitroimidazole class, is used against protozoa.
Ifenprodil is an atypical noncompetitive antagonist at the NMDA receptor, it interacts with high affinity at a homogeneous population of NMDA receptors in neonatal rat forebrain with IC50 of 0.3 μM.

Tetrabenazine(Nitoman, Xenazine) acts primarily as a reversible high-affinity inhibitor of mono-amine uptake into granular vesicles of presynaptic neurons by binding selectively to VMAT-2 Also blocks dopamine D2 receptors, but this affinity is 1,000-fold lower than its affinity for VMAT-2.
Idramantone is an immune agonist.
Ponatinib (AP24534) is a novel, potent multi-target inhibitor of Abl, PDGFRα, VEGFR2, FGFR1 and Src with IC50 of 0.37 nM, 1.1 nM, 1.5 nM, 2.2 nM and 5.4 nM in cell-free assays, respectively.
Citiolone is a derivative of the amino acid cysteine, used in liver therapy.

S-Ruxolitinib is the chirality of INCB018424, which is the first potent, selective, JAK1/2 inhibitor to enter the clinic with IC50 of 3.3 nM/2.8 nM, >130-fold selectivity for JAK1/2 versus JAK3. Phase 3.
Taurine is an organic acid widely distributed in animal tissues.
Temsirolimus (CCI-779, NSC 683864) is a specific mTOR inhibitor with IC50 of 1.76 μM in a cell-free assay.
Terbinafine is used to treat infections caused by a fungus. It works by killing the fungus or preventing its growth.
Telmisartan  is an angiotensin II receptor antagonist (ARB) used in the management of hypertension.
Azelaic acid is an organic compound produced by the ozonolysis of oleic acid and possesses antibacterial, keratolytic, comedolytic, and anti-oxidant activity.
Sotagliflozin (LX4211) is an oral dual SGLT1/SGLT2 inhibitor with IC50 of 36 nM and 1.8 nM, respectively. Phase 3.
Estradiol cypionate is the 17 β-cyclopentylpropinate ester of estradiol, which inhibits ET-1 synthesis via estrogen receptor.

Niraparib (MK-4827) is a selective inhibitor of PARP1/2 with IC50 of 3.8 nM/2.1 nM, with great activity in cancer cells with mutant BRCA-1 and BRCA-2. It is >330-fold selective against PARP3, V-PARP and Tank1. Phase 3.
Domiphen bromide is a quaternary ammonium antiseptic with actions as a cationic surfactant.
Gentamycin Sulfate is a broad-spectrum, aminoglycoside antibiotic used for cell culture which inhibits protein synthesis in sensitive organisms.
Drospirenone is a synthetic progestin that is an analog to spironolactone.
Rapamycin (Sirolimus) is a specific mTOR inhibitor with IC50 of ~0.1 nM HEK293 cells.
Difluprednate (difluoroprednisolone butyrate acetate, or DFBA) is a synthetic difluorinated prednisolone derivative, it is originally developed for dermatologic applications.
Mizoribine is an imidazole nucleoside, selectively inhibits inosine monophosphate synthetase and guanosine monophosphate synthetase.
Carbidopa is an aromatic-L-amino-acid decarboxylase inhibitor with an IC50 of 29 ± 2 μM.
Diatrizoate sodium is an iodinated radiopaque X-ray contrast medium that is used as a diagnostic aid in angiography, urography and radiography.
Pheniramine Maleate is an antihistamine with anticholinergic properties used to treat allergic conditions such as hay fever or urticaria.

Acetylcysteine(N-acetyl-l-cysteine) is a ROS(reactive oxygen species) inhibitor that antagonizes the activity of proteasome inhibitors. It is also a tumor necrosis factor production inhibitor, used mainly as a mucolytic, protects against acetaminophen overdose-induced hepatotoxicity by maintaining or restoring hepatic concentrations of glutathione.

Acotiamide Hydrochloride is the hydrochloride salt form of acotiamide, a prokinetic agent with gastrointestinal (GI) motility-enhancing activity. It is a new orally active selective acetylcholinesterase inhibitor.
Epinastine is an antihistamine and mast cell stabilizer that is used in eye drops to treat allergic conjunctivitis.
Zanamivir is a neuraminidase inhibitor used in the treatment and prophylaxis of influenza caused by influenza A virus and influenza B virus.
Rosuvastatin Calcium is a competitive inhibitor of HMG-CoA reductase with IC50 of 11 nM in a cell-free assay.
Nicotinamide (Vitamin B3), a water-soluble vitamin, is an active component of coenzymes NAD and NADP, and also act as an inhibitor of sirtuins.
Urethane is a kind of antineoplastic agent that is also used as a veterinary anesthetic. It is a intermediate in organic synthesis.
TAK-700 (Orteronel) is a potent and highly selective human 17,20-lyase inhibitor with IC50 of 38 nM, exhibits >1000-fold selectivity over other CYPs (e.g. 11-hydroxylase and CYP3A4). Phase 3.

Semagacestat (LY450139) is a γ-secretase blocker for Aβ42, Aβ40 and Aβ38 with IC50 of 10.9 nM, 12.1 nM and 12.0 nM, also inhibits Notch signaling with IC50 of 14.1 nM in H4 human glioma cell. Phase 3.
Orotic acid(6-Carboxyuracil) is a heterocyclic compound and an acid.

Iopromide is a low osmolar, non-ionic X-ray contrast agent for intravascular administration. It functions as a contrast agent by opacifying blood vessels in the path of flow of the contrast agent, permitting radiographic visualization of the internal structures until significant hemodilution occurs.
Fomepizole is a competitive inhibitor of alcohol dehydrogenase, the enzyme that catalyzes the initial steps in the metabolism of ethylene glycol and methanol to their toxic metabolites.
Tafluprost is a novel prostaglandin analog with a high affinity for the fluoroprostaglandin (FP) receptor PGF2α. A prostanoid selective FP receptor agonist.
Methscopolamine is a muscarinic acetylcholine receptor blocker.
Epinephrine HCl is a hormone and a neurotransmitter.
abemaciclib (LY2835219) is a potent and selective inhibitor of CDK4 and CDK6 with IC50 of 2 nM and 10 nM in cell-free assays, respectively. Phase 3.

S-(+)-Rolipram inhibits human monocyte cyclic AMP-specific PDE4 with IC50 of 0.75 μM, has anti-inflammatory and anti-depressant activity in the central nervous system, less potent than its R enantiomer.
Canagliflozin is a highly potent and selective SGLT2 inhibitor for hSGLT2 with IC50 of 2.2 nM in a cell-free assay, exhibits 413-fold selectivity over hSGLT1.

Omipalisib (GSK2126458, GSK458) is a highly selective and potent inhibitor of p110α/β/δ/γ, mTORC1/2 with Ki of 0.019 nM/0.13 nM/0.024 nM/0.06 nM and 0.18 nM/0.3 nM in cell-free assays, respectively. Phase 1.
Terbutaline Sulfate is a selective β2-adrenergic receptor agonist with IC50 of 53 nM.
Dibutyryl-cAMP (Bucladesine) is a cell-permeable PKA activator by mimicing the action of endogenous cAMP.
Adefovir Dipivoxil is a reverse transcriptase inhibitor, used in the treatment of chronic hepatitis B virus (HBV).
Pexidartinib (PLX3397) is an oral, potent mutil-targeted receptor tyrosine kinase inhibitor of CSF-1R, Kit, and Flt3 with IC50 of 20 nM, 10 nM and 160 nM, respectively. Phase 3.

Dyclonine HCl is a hydrochloride salt form of dyclonine which is an oral anaesthetic, reversibly binds to activated sodium channels on the neuronal membrane, thereby decreasing the neuronal membrane's permeability to sodium ions, leading to an increased threshold for excitation.

Ricolinostat (ACY-1215) is a selective HDAC6 inhibitor with IC50 of 5 nM in a cell-free assay. It is >10-fold more selective for HDAC6 than HDAC1/2/3 (class I HDACs) with slight activity against HDAC8, minimal activity against HDAC4/5/7/9/11, Sirtuin1, and Sirtuin2. Phase 2.
Dinitolmide is a broad-spectrum anticoccidial drug.
Azasetron HCl is a selective 5-HT3 receptor antagonist with IC50 of 0.33 nM used in the management of nausea and vomiting induced by cancer chemotherapy.
Mestranol is the 3-methyl ether of ethinyl estradiol, which is a potent estrogen receptor agonist and used as oral contraceptives.
Defactinib (VS-6063, PF-04554878) is a selective, and orally active FAK inhibitor. Phase 2.
Betamethasone is a glucocorticoid steroid with anti-inflammatory and immunosuppressive properties.

Butoconazole nitrate is an anti-fungal agent that inhibits PHA-stimulated release of cytokines-- IL-2, TNFα, IFN and GM-CSF from human peripheral blood lymphocytes (IC50 of 7.2 μg/mL, 14.4 μg/mL, 7.36 μg/mL and 7.6 μg/mL, respectively).
Epirubicin HCl, a semisynthetic L-arabino derivative of doxorubicin, is an antineoplastic agent by inhibiting Topoisomerase.
Pyridoxine HCl is a form of vitamin B6.
Deoxycorticosterone acetate is a steroid hormone used for intramuscular injection for replacement therapy of the adrenocortical steroid.
Cefmenoxime, a potent inhibitor of Enterobacteriaceae, is a cephalosporin antibiotic that is administered intravenously or intramuscularly.
Doxifluridine is an oral prodrug that is converted to the cytotoxic agent 5-fluorouracil (5-FU).

Pixantrone is a novel aza-anthracenedione compound with antitumor activity. It is a weak topoisomerase II inhibitor and forms stable DNA adducts through alkylation with specificity for DNA hypermethylated sites.
Fostamatinib (R788), a prodrug of the active metabolite R406, is a Syk inhibitor with IC50 of 41 nM, strongly inhibits Syk but not Lyn, 5-fold less potent to Flt3. Phase 3.
Chloroquine phosphate is a 4-aminoquinoline anti-malarial and anti-rheumatoid agent, also acting as an ATM activator.

Palbociclib (PD0332991) Isethionate is a highly selective inhibitor of CDK4/6 with IC50 of 11 nM/16 nM in cell-free assays. It shows no activity against CDK1/2/5, EGFR, FGFR, PDGFR, InsR, etc. Phase 3.
Amitriptyline inhibits serotonin receptor, norepinephrine receptor, 5-HT4, 5-HT2 and sigma 1 receptor with IC50 of 3.45 nM, 13.3 nM, 7.31 nM, 235 nM and 287 nM, respectively.
Megestrol acetate is a synthetic progestogen, used to treat breast cancer and loss of appetite.
Xylose is a sugar first isolated from wood.
Lafutidine, a newly developed histamine H(2)-receptor antagonist, inhibits gastric acid secretion.

Vitamin E is a fat-soluble vitamin with potent antioxidant properties. It is a potent peroxyl radical scavenger and inhibits noncompetitively cyclooxygenase activity in many tissues, also inhibits angiogenesis and tumor dormancy through suppressing vascular endothelial growth factor (VEGF) gene transcription.
Mirabegron is a selective β3-adrenoceptor agonist with EC50 of 22.4 nM.
Roxatidine Acetate HCl is a specific and competitive histamin H2-receptor antagonist, with IC50 of 3.2 μM, inhibits gastric acid secretion and ulcer formation.
Carbasalate calcium is an analgesic, antipyretic, and anti-inflammatory drug as well as a platelet aggregation inhibitor.
Mifepristone is a remarkably active antagonist of progesterone receptor and glucocorticoid receptor with IC50 of 0.2 nM and 2.6 nM, respectively.
Cilengitide is a potent integrin inhibitor for αvβ3 receptor and αvβ5 receptor with IC50 of 4.1 nM and 79 nM in cell-free assays, respectively ~10-fold selectivity against gpIIbIIIa. Phase 2.
Chlormezanone，a non-benzodiazepine that is used in the management of anxiety. It has been suggested for use in the treatment of muscle spasm.
Velpatasvir is a second-generation NS5A inhibitor that inhibits hepatitis C viral replication through acting on the crucial membranous web that facilitates RNA replication.

Cabazitaxel is a semi-synthetic derivative of a natural taxoid that kills cancer cells by inhibiting cell division and growth. Cabazitaxel exerts its effects by inhibiting microtubule growth and assembly, processes that are essential for cells to divide.
Balsalazide Disodium is the disodium salt form of balsalazide, an aminosalicylate and oral prodrug that is enzymatically cleaved in the colon to produce the anti-inflammatory agent mesalazine.
Rosiglitazone, a member of the thiazolidinedione class of antihyperglycaemic agents, is a high-affinity selective agonist of the peroxisome proliferator-activated receptor-γ with IC50 of 42 nM.
Carteolol HCl is a β-adrenoceptor antagonist, used for the treatment of glaucoma.
Indapamide is a non-thiazide sulphonamide diuretic compound, generally used in the treatment of hypertension, as well as decompensated cardiac failure.
Nikethamide is a respiratory stimulant that acts directly in the respiratory centres of brain.
Cortisone acetate (Cortone) is an acetate salt form of cortisone that is a steroid hormone and a glucocorticoid.
Zaltoprofen is an inhibitor of COX-1 and COX-2 for treatment of arthritis.
Rifapentine is an antibiotic, which inhibits DNA-dependent RNA polymerase activity, used to treat tuberculosis.
Avobenzone is an oil soluble ingredient used in sunscreen products to absorb the full spectrum of UVA rays and a dibenzoylmethane derivative.
Tofogliflozin is a novel sodium-glucose co-transporter 2(SGLT2) inhibitor with IC50 values of 2.9 nM and 8444 nM for hSGLT2 and hSGLT1, respectively.
Penicillin G Sodium is a β-lactam antibiotic produced by Penicillin spp.
Isradipine is a potent and selective L-type voltage-gated calcium channel blocker, used to treat high blood pressure.
Mebeverine, a 3-phenylethylamine derivative of methoxybenzamine, acts as a musculotropic antispasmodic agent.
Phenazopyridine HCl is a local analgesic that has been used in urinary tract disorders. It is an inhibitor of sodium channel protein type 1 subunit alpha.
Melphalan is a phenylalanine derivative of nitrogen mustard with antineoplastic activity.
Dirithromycin is a macrolide glycopeptide antibiotic by binding to the 50S subunit of the 70S bacterial ribosome to inhibit the translocation of peptides.
Raloxifene is an estrogen antagonist, which inhibits human cytosolic aldehyde oxidase-catalyzed phthalazine oxidation activity with IC50 of 5.7 nM.
Mirtazapine is an adrenergic and seroton receptor antagonist, used to treat depression.
Phenindione is an anticoagulant which functions as a Vitamin K antagonist.
Anagrelide is a drug used for the treatment of essential thrombocytosis.
Sulfinpyrazone is one of the most studied platelet COX inhibitors, also a uricosuric agent that competitively inhibits uric acid reabsorption in kidney proximal tubules.
Didanosine is a reverse transcriptase inhibitor with an IC50 of 0.49 μM.

Diclofenac diethylamine is a nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drug taken to reduce inflammation and as an analgesic reducing pain in certain conditions. Diclofenac exerts its action via inhibition of prostaglandin synthesis by inhibiting cyclooxygenase-1 (COX-1) and cyclooxygenase-2 (COX-2) with relative equipotency.
Nifedipine is a dihydropyridine calcium channel blocker, used to lower hypertension and to treat angina.
Cilnidipine is a unique L-type and N-type calcium channel blocker, used for high blood pressure treatment.
Clarithromycin is a macrolide antibiotic and a CYP3A4 inhibitor, used to treat a number of bacterial infections.
Rebamipide is a cholecystokinin type 1 (CCK1) receptor inhibitor for inhibiting [125I]BH-CCK-8S with IC50 of 37.7 μM.
Mefloquine HCl is a blood schizonticide by inhibiting hemozoin formation, used as an antimalarial drug.
Empagliflozin (BI-10773) is a potent and selective SGLT-2 inhibitor with IC50 of 3.1 nM, exhibits >300-fold selectivity over SGLT-1, 4, 5 and 6. Phase 3.
Etoposide is a semisynthetic derivative of podophyllotoxin, which inhibits DNA synthesis via topoisomerase II  inhibition activity.
Acetylleucine is a drug used in the treatment of vertigo.
Methocarbamol is a carbonic anhydrase inhibitor, used as a central muscle relaxant to treat skeletal muscle spasms.
Calcifediol is a major circulating metabolite of vitamin D3 and acts as a competitive inhibitor with an apparent Ki of 3.9 μM. It also suppresses PTH secretion and mRNA (ED50=2 nM).
Amiloride is a selective T-type calcium channel blocker, an epithelial sodium channel blocker and a selective inhibitor of urokinase plasminogen activator (uPA)(Ki=7 μM).
Diazoxide is a well-known small molecule that activates KATP channels in the smooth muscle of blood vessels and pancreatic beta-cells by increasing membrane permeability to potassium ions.
Lesinurad is a selective uric acid reabsorption inhibitor (SURI) under investigation for treatment of gout in combination with xanthine oxidase inhibitors.
Bezafibrate is the first clinically tested dual and pan-PPAR co-agonism.
Losmapimod (GW856553X) is a selective, potent, and orally active p38 MAPK inhibitor with pKi of 8.1 and 7.6 for p38α and p38β, respectively. Phase 3.
Pemetrexed Disodium Hydrate is a novel antifolate and antimetabolite for TS, DHFR and GARFT with Ki of 1.3 nM, 7.2 nM and 65 nM, respectively.
Perphenazine is a phenothiazine derivative and a dopamine antagonist with antiemetic and antipsychotic properties.
Rosiglitazone HCl is a blood glucose-lowering drugs, stimulating insulin secretion by binding to the PPAR receptors in fat cells.
Cilostazol is a potent cyclic nucleotide phosphodiesterase type 3 (PDE3) inhibitor with IC50 of 0.2 μM and inhibitor of adenosine uptake.
Daptomycin is a novel antibiotic with rapid in vitro bactericidal activity against gram-positive organisms.
Decamethonium Bromide is a nicotinic AChR partial agonist and neuromuscular blocking agent.
Pralidoxime is an antidote to organophosphate pesticides and chemicals An acetylcholinesterase (AChE) reactivator.

Silmitasertib (CX-4945) is a potent and selective inhibitor of CK2 (casein kinase 2) with IC50 of 1 nM in a cell-free assay, less potent to Flt3, Pim1 and CDK1 (inactive in cell-based assay). Phase 1/2.
Sulfamerazine is a sulfonamide antibacterial.
Bucetin is an analgesic and antipyretice agent with a risk of carcinogenesis.
Tipiracil is an inhibitor of thymidine phosphorylase, the enzyme that degrades trifluridine into trifluorothymidine. Its combination with trifluridine increases the bioavailability of trifluridine.
Cetylpyridinium chloride is a cationic quaternary ammonium compound used as oropharyngeal antiseptic.
CUDC-101 is a potent multi-targeted inhibitor against HDAC, EGFR and HER2 with IC50 of 4.4 nM, 2.4 nM, and 15.7 nM, and inhibits class I/II HDACs, but not class III, Sir-type HDACs. Phase 1.
Itraconazole is a relatively potent inhibitor of CYP3A4 with IC50 of 6.1 nM, used as a triazole antifungal agent.
Afatinib (BIBW2992) inhibits EGFR/ErbB irreversibly in vitro with IC50 of 0.5, 0.4, 10, 14, 1 nM for EGFRwt, EGFR L858R , EGFR L858R/T790M ErbB2 (HER2) and ErbB4 (HER4), respectively.

Rosiglitazone is a potent antihyperglycemic agent and a potent thiazolidinedione insulin sensitizer with IC50 of 12, 4 and 9 nM for rat, 3T3-L1 and human adipocytes, respectively. Rosiglitazone is a pure ligand of PPAR-gamma, and has no PPAR-alpha-binding action.
Axitinib is a multi-target inhibitor of VEGFR1, VEGFR2, VEGFR3, PDGFRβ and c-Kit with IC50 of 0.1 nM, 0.2 nM, 0.1-0.3 nM, 1.6 nM and 1.7 nM in Porcine aorta endothelial cells, respectively.
Azacitidine is a nucleoside analogue of cytidine that specifically inhibits DNA methylation by trapping DNA methyltransferases.
Tetrahydrozoline HCl is an imidazoline derivative with alpha receptor agonist activity.
Solifenacin succinate is a urinary antispasmodic of the antimuscarinic class.
Carbamazepine (Carbatrol) is a sodium channel blocker with IC50 of 131 μM in rat brain synaptosomes.
Stavudine (d4T) is a nucleoside analog reverse transcriptase inhibitor (NARTI) active against HIV.
L-Adrenaline belongs to a group of the compounds known as catecholamines.
Dexmedetomidine is a sedative medication used by intensive care units and anesthetists.
Felodipine is a selective L-type Ca2+ channel blocker with IC50 of 0.15 nM.
Articaine is a dental local anesthetic which contains an additional ester group that is metabolized by estearases in blood and tissue.
Dronedarone HCl is a multichannel blocker targeting potassium channel, sodium channel and calcium channel, used as an antiarrhythmic drug for treatment of atrial fibrillation (AF).
Ciclopirox is a broad-spectrum antifungal agent working as an iron chelator.
Risperidone is a mutil-targeted antagonist for dopamine, serotonin, adrenergic and histamine receptors, used to treat schizophrenia and bipolar disorder.
Flunixin Meglumin is a potent inhibitor of the enzyme cyclooxygenase (COX) used as analgesic agent with anti-inflammatory and antipyretic activity.
Bendamustine HCL is a DNA-damaging agent with IC50 of 50 μM in cell-free assay.
Pirfenidone is an inhibitor for TGF-β production and TGF-β stimulated collagen production, reduces production of TNF-α and IL-1β, and also has anti-fibrotic and anti-inflammatory properties. Phase 3.
Cyclobenzaprine HCl is a muscle relaxant by blocking pain sensations, used for the treatment of muscle spasms A 5-HT2 receptor antagonist.
Naratriptan HCl is a triptan agent that is used for the treatment of migraine headaches.
Nitrofural is a topical anti-infective agent with an IC50 of 22.83 ± 1.2 μM. (Rat LD50 = 590 mg/kg)
Trametinib (GSK1120212) is a highly specific and potent MEK1/2 inhibitor with IC50 of 0.92 nM/1.8 nM in cell-free assays, no inhibition of the kinase activities of c-Raf, B-Raf, ERK1/2.
Bosentan is an endothelin (ET) receptor antagonist for ET-A and ET-B with Ki of 4.7 nM and 95 nM, respectively.
Sodium phenylbutyrate is a histone deacetylase inhibitor, used to treat urea cycle disorders.
Carmofur is a highly potent acid ceramidase inhibitor, used in the treatment of breast and colorectal cancer.
Zolmitriptan is a novel and highly selective 5-HT(1B/1D) receptor agonist, used in the treatment of acute migraines.
Olsalazine Sodium is an anti-inflammatory prodrug, which consists of two 5-ASA moieties linked by an azo bond.

Elagolix Soidum is a potent, selective, orally active, non-peptide antagonist of the gonadotropin-releasing hormone receptor (GnRHR) with Kd value of 54 pM. Concentration at 10 μM shows no significant activity on ion channels, enzymes, and transporters (inhibition <50%).
Tamoxifen is an antagonist of the estrogen receptor in breast tissue.
Ezetimibe is a potent, selective, cholesterol absorption inhibitor, used to lower cholesterol.
Naftopidil is a selective α1-adrenergic receptor antagonist with Ki of 3.7 nM, 20 nM, and 1.2 nM for α1a, α1b, and α1d, respectively, used for the treatment of benign prostatic hyperplasia.
Lonidamine is an orally administered small molecule hexokinase inactivator.
Tinidazole is an anti-parasitic drug.

Mocetinostat (MGCD0103) is a potent HDAC inhibitor with most potency for HDAC1 with IC50 of 0.15 μM in a cell-free assay, 2- to 10- fold selectivity against HDAC2, 3, and 11, and no activity to HDAC4, 5, 6, 7, and 8. Phase 2.
Camphor is a waxy, flammable, white or transparent solid with a strong aroma, often used to relieve pain, reduce itching and treat fungal infections. It can activate TRPV1  and TRPV3.
Pitavastatin calcium, a novel member of the medication class of statins, is a calcium salt formulation of pitavastatin which is a highly effective HMG-CoA reductase inhibitor.
Timolol Maleate is a non-selective, beta-adrenergic receptor antagonist for β1/β2 with Ki of 1.97 nM/2.0 nM.
Pantoprazole is a proton pump inhibitor used for short-term treatment of erosion and ulceration of the esophagus caused by gastroesophageal reflux disease.
Scopolamine HBr is a competitive muscarinic acetylcholine receptor with an IC50 of 55.3 nM.
Dextrose, a simple sugar (monosaccharide), is an important carbohydrate in biology.
Ceftriaxone sodium trihydrate is a third-generation cephalosporin antibiotic.
Gallamine Triethiodide  is a cholinergic receptor blocker with an IC50 of 68.0 ± 8.4 μM.
Clindamycin palmitate HCl is a water soluble hydrochloride salt of the ester of clindamycin and palmitic acid and a lincosamide antibiotic.
Methyldopa (Aldomet) is a DOPA decarboxylase competitive inhibitor with an ED50 of 21.8 mg/kg.
Amikacin is an aminoglycoside antibiotic used to treat different types of bacterial infections.
Nilotinib (AMN-107) is a selective Bcr-Abl inhibitor with IC50 less than 30 nM in Murine myeloid progenitor cells.

Idarubicin HCl is a hydrochloride salt form of Idarubicin which is an anthracycline antibiotic and a DNA topoisomerase II (topo II) inhibitor for MCF-7 cells with IC50 of 3.3 ng/mL in a cell-free assay.
Ethambutol is a bacteriostatic antimycobacterial agent, which obstructs the formation of cell wall by inhibiting arabinosyl transferases.

Idelalisib (CAL-101, GS-1101) is a selective p110δ inhibitor with IC50 of 2.5 nM in cell-free assays shown to have 40- to 300-fold greater selectivity for p110δ than p110α/β/γ, and 400- to 4000-fold more selectivity to p110δ than C2β, hVPS34, DNA-PK and mTOR.

Dapsone, also known as diaminodiphenyl sulfone (DDS), is an antibiotic commonly used in combination with rifampicin and clofazimine for the treatment of leprosy.

Ranolazine is a calcium uptake inhibitor via the sodium/calcium channel, used to treat chronic angina.

Lidocaine is a selective inverse peripheral histamine H1-receptor agonist with an IC50 of >32 μM.
Granisetron is a serotonin 5-HT3 receptor antagonist,used to treat chemotherapy-induced nausea and vomiting.
Protirelin is a tripeptide that stimulates the release of thyrotropin and prolactin.
Pergolide Mesylate is an antiparkinsonian agent which functions as a dopaminergic agonist.
Sulbactam sodium (Unasyn) is an irreversible β-lactamase inhibitor.
Gabapentin HCl is a GABA analogue, used to treat seizures and neuropathic pain.
Cefotiam hydrochloride is the hydrochloride salt form of cefotiam and has a broad spectrum of activity against both gram-positive and gram-negative microorganisms.
Isepamicin Sulphate is an aminoglycoside antibiotic, which inhibits bacterial protein synthesis by targeting the bacterial 30S ribosomal subunit.
Tamibarotene is a synthetic retinoic acid receptor (RAR) agonist with high specificity for RARα and RARβ over RARγ.
Glipizide is used to treat high blood sugar levels caused by a type of diabetes mellitus called type 2 diabetes.
Chloramphenicol is a bacteriostatic by inhibiting protein synthesis.

Ataluren (PTC124) selectively induces ribosomal read-through of premature but not normal termination codons, with EC50 of 0.1 μM in HEK293 cells, may provide treatment for genetic disorders caused by nonsense mutations (e.g. CF caused by CFTR nonsense mutation). Phase 3.

Imatinib Mesylate (STI571) is an orally bioavailability mesylate salt of Imatinib, which is a multi-target inhibitor of v-Abl, c-Kit and PDGFR with IC50 of 0.6 μM, 0.1 μM and 0.1 μM in cell-free or cell-based assays, respectively.

Zosuquidar (LY335979) 3HCl is a potent modulator of P-glycoprotein-mediated multi-drug resistance with Ki of 60 nM in a cell-free assay. Phase 3.

Crisaborole is a small-molecule, boron-based, selective PDE4 inhibitor and has broad-spectrum anti-inflammatory activity.
Dipyridamole (Persantine) is a phosphodiesterase inhibitor that blocks uptake and metabolism of adenosine by erythrocytes and vascular endothelial cells.
Efinaconazole is an inhibitor of 14 alpha-demethylase which is involved in the biosynthesis of ergosterol, a constituent of fungal cell membranes.
Uridine is a nucleoside, contains a uracil attached to a ribose ring via a β-N1-glycosidic bond.
Chloroxylenol is a broad-spectrum antimicrobial chemical compound used to control bacteria, algae, fungi and virus.

DL-Carnitine HCl is a quaternary ammonium compound biosynthesized from the amino acids lysine and methionine.
Hexestrol binds to ERα and ERβ with EC50 of 0.07 nM and 0.175 nM, respectively.

Thalidomide was introduced as a sedative drug, immunomodulatory agent and also is investigated for treating symptoms of many cancers. Thalidomide inhibits an E3 ubiquitin ligase, which is a CRBN-DDB1-Cul4A complex.
Hexachlorophene is a potent KCNQ1/KCNE1 potassium channel activator with EC50 of 4.61 ± 1.29 μM It can also attenuate Wnt/beta-catenin signaling through the Siah-1-mediated beta-catenin degradation.
Erlotinib HCl (OSI-744) is an EGFR inhibitor with IC50 of 2 nM in cell-free assays, >1000-fold more sensitive for EGFR than human c-Src or v-Abl.
Citric acid trilithium salt tetrahydrate is a pharmaceutical and construction material. It is commonly used in HPLC gradient elution for quantification of amino acids.

Ebastine is a potent H1-histamine receptor antagonist, used for allergic disorders.
Venetoclax (ABT-199, GDC-0199) is a Bcl-2-selective inhibitor with Ki of <0.01 nM in cell-free assays, >4800-fold more selective versus Bcl-xL and Bcl-w, and no activity to Mcl-1. Phase 3.

Cefazolin Sodium is a semisynthetic cephalosporin analog with broad-spectrum antibiotic action due to inhibition of bacterial cell wall synthesis. It attains high serum levels and is excreted quickly via the urine.
Fenbufen is an orally active phenylalkanoic derivative with anti-inflammatory, analgesic and antipyretic activity. It is a non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drug.
Mycophenolate Mofetil is a non-competitive, selective and reversible inhibitor of inosine monophosphate dehydrogenase I/II with IC50 of 39 nM and 27 nM, respectively.
Tranexamic Acid is an antifibrinolytic for blocking lysine-binding sites of plasmin and elastase-derived plasminogen fragments with IC50 of 5 mM.
Pimavanserin is a potent and selective serotonin 5-HT2A inverse agonist with pIC50 of 8.73, used to treat psychosis associated with Parkinson’s disease.
Lomefloxacin HCl is a hydrochloride salt of lomefloxacin and is a fluoroquinolone antibiotic.
Tazarotene is a retinoid prodrug of tazarotenic acid, which is a RAR agonist, used to treat psoriasis, acne, and sun damaged skin.

Terconazole is a new, broad-spectrum, triazole antifungal agent which is primarily used to treat vaginal fungal infections.
Vilanterol trifenatate is a novel inhaled long-acting beta2 adrenoceptor agonist with inherent 24-hour activity for once daily treatment of COPD and asthma.
Sertraline HCl is a 5-HT antagonist with Ki of 13 nM.
Vitamin A is a group of unsaturated nutritional hydrocarbons, that includes retinol, retinal, retinoic acid, and several provitamin A carotenoids, among which beta-carotene is the most important.

CB1954(Tretazicar) is a anticancer prodrug that is converted in the presence of the enzyme NQO2 and co-substrate caricotamide ( EP-0152R) (EP) into a potent cytotoxic bifunctional alkylating agent. It can be activated by NAD(P)H quinone oxidoreductase 2.
Tetracycline HCl is a hydrochloride salt of tetracycline that is a broad-spectrum polyketide antibiotic.

Tazobactam is a β-lactamases Inhibitor with antibacterial activity. It also inhibits the class D oxacillinase OXA-2. It is used in combination with piperacillin and other β-lactam antibiotics to broaden their spectrum and enhance their effect.
Bicalutamide is an androgen receptor (AR) antagonist with IC50 of 0.16 μM in LNCaP/AR(cs)cell line.
Flibanserin is a nonhormonal, centrally acting molecule that acts as an agonist at postsynaptic 5-HT1A receptors and as an antagonist at 5-HT2A receptors.
Diethylcarbamazine citrate is an inhibitor of arachidonic acid metabolism in filarial microfilaria and is highly specific for several parasites and does not contain any toxic metallic elements.
Motolimod (VTX-2337) is a selective and potent Toll-like receptor (TLR) 8 agonist with EC50 of 100 nM, > 50-fold selectivity over TLR7. Phase 2.

Trimetazidine dihydrochloride is a kind of drug for treatment of chronic ischemic disorders. It improves myocardial glucose utilization through inhibition of fatty acid metabolism, known as fatty acid oxidation inhibitor.
Penicillamine is used as an antirheumatic and as a chelating agent in Wilson’s disease.
Ouabain is a selective Na+/K+, -ATPase inhibitor, binds to α2 /α3 subunit with Ki of 41 nM/15 nM.
Sulfamethizole is a sulfathiazole antibacterial agent.

Thimerosal is a well-established antiseptic and antifungal agent and usually used as a preservative in vaccines, immunoglobulin preparations, skin test antigens, antivenins, ophthalmic and nasal products, and tattoo inks.
Tylosin tartrate is a macrolide antibiotic approved for the control of mycoplasmosis in poultry.

Tenofovir Disoproxil Fumarate belongs to a class of antiretroviral drugs, it inhibits the activity of HIV reverse transcriptase by competing with the natural substrate deoxyadenosine 5’-triphosphate and, after incorporation into DNA, by DNA chain termination.

Glycine is a non-essential, non-polar, non-optical, glucogenic amino acid that is primarily found in gelatin and silk fibroin. It is involved in the body's production of DNA, phospholipids and collagen, and in release of energy.

AmbroxolHCl is a potent inhibitor of the neuronal Na+ channels, inhibits TTX-resistant Na+ currents with IC50 of 35.2 μM and 22.5 μM for tonic and phasic block, inhibits TTX-sensitive Na+ currents with IC50 of 100 μM. Phase 3.
Sodium benzoate is a preservative and uesd as a food additive which is bacteriostatic and fungistatic under acidic conditions.

Curcumin is the principal curcuminoid of the popular Indian spice turmeric, which is a member of the ginger family (Zingiberaceae). It is an inhibitor of p300 histone acetylatransferase（IC50~25 μM） and Histone deacetylase activates Nrf2 pathway and supresses the activation of transcription factor NF-κB.
Edoxaban is a selective factor Xa inhibitor with Ki of 0.561 nM, >10 000-fold selectivity over thrombin and FIXa, and is also an orally bioavailable anticoagulant drug.
Amonafide produces protein-associated DNA-strand breaks through a topoisomerase II-mediated reaction, but does not produce topoisomerase I-mediated DNA cleavage. Phase 3.
Nelfinavir Mesylate is a potent HIV protease inhibitor with Ki of 2 nM.
Alibendol is an antispasmodic,choleretic, and cholekinetic.
Sodium Ascorbate is a more bioavailable form of vitamin C that is an alternative to taking ascorbic acid as a supplement.
Hyoscyamine is an AChR inhibitor with IC50 of 7.5 nM.
Trichlormethiazide is a diuretic with properties similar to those of hydrochlorothiazide.
Argatroban is a potent and selective synthetic thrombin inhibitor with Ki ranging from 5 nM to 39 nM, used as an anticoagulant.
Evacetrapib (LY2484595) is a potent and selective inhibitor of CETP with IC50 of 5.5 nM, elevates HDL cholesterol without increases in aldosterone or blood pressure. Phase 3.
Sulfamethoxazole sodium is an antibiotic used for bacterial infections.
Tolmetin is a nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drug of the heterocyclic acetic acid derivative class and also exhibits analgesic and antipyretic activity.
Piroxicam is a non-selective COX inhibitor, used in the treatment of rheumatoid and osteoarthritis.

Ibutilide Fumarate is a Class III antiarrhythmic agent that is indicated for acute cardioconversion of atrial fibrillation and atrial flutter of a recent onset to sinus rhythm by induction of slow inward sodium current, which prolongs action potential and refractory period of myocardial cells.
Cladribine is an adenosine deaminase inhibitor for U266, RPMI8226, and MM1.S cells with IC50 of approximately 2.43 μM, 0.75 μM, and 0.18 μM, respectively.
Masitinib is a novel inhibitor for Kit and PDGFRα/β with IC50 of 200 nM and 540 nM/800 nM, weak inhibition to ABL and c-Fms. Phase 3.
Paroxetine HCl is an antidepressant drug of the SSRI type.

Calcipotriene is a synthetic derivative of calcitriol, a form of vitamin D. It can induce differentiation and suppresses proliferation of keratinocytes, reversing abnormal keratinocyte changes in psoriasis, and lead to normalization of epidermal growth.
Ceftazidime is a third-generation cephalosporin that has activity against Gram-negative bacilli, including Pseudomonas aeruginosa.
Hydrocortisone is a steroid hormone or glucocorticoid produced by the adrenal gland.
Flunarizine 2HCl is a dihydrochloride salt form which is a calcium channel blocker with a Ki of 68 nM.
Dihydroartemisinin (DHA) is a semi-synthetic derivative of artemisinin and isolated from the traditional Chinese herb Artemisia annua.
Tetracaine HCl is a hydrochloride salt form of tetracaine which is a potent local anaesthetic and a channel function allosteric inhibitor.
Rilpivirine is a non-nucleoside reverse transcriptase inhibitor (NNRTI), and used to treat HIV-1 infection.
Propylthiouracil is a thyroperoxidase and 5'-deiodinase inhibitor, used to treat hyperthyroidism.
Cytarabine is an antimetabolic agent and DNA synthesis inhibitor with IC50 of 16 nM in wild-type CCRF-CEM cells.
Cimetidine, a histamine congener, competitively inhibits histamine binding to histamine H2 receptors.

Mupirocin Calcium is the calcium salt form of mupirocin, a natural crotonic acid derivative extracted from Pseudomonas fluorescens,which inhibits bacterial protein synthesis and is used as an antibiotic.

Hydroxychloroquine Sulfate is an antimalarial agent used for the treatment of systemic lupus erythematosus, rheumatoid arthritis and other autoimmune, inflammatory and dermatologic conditions. Also acts as an inhibitor of autophagy and toll-like receptor (TLR) 7/9.
Saccharin is an artificial sweetener with effectively no food energy.
Cefdinir is an oral cephalosporin antibiotic, used to treat bacterial infections in many different parts of the body.

Fexofenadine inhibits histamine H1 receptor with IC50 of 246 nM.
Gemcitabine HCl is a DNA synthesis inhibitor with IC50 of 50 nM, 40 nM, 18 nM and 12 nM in PANC1, MIAPaCa2, BxPC3 and Capan2 cells, respectively.
Dabrafenib (GSK2118436) is a mutant BRAFV600 specific inhibitor with IC50 of 0.8 nM in cell-free assays, with 4- and 6-fold less potency against B-Raf(wt) and c-Raf, respectively.
Niraparib (MK-4827) tosylate is a selective inhibitor of PARP1/PARP2 with IC50 of 3.8 nM/2.1 nM.
Torsemide is a pyridyl sulfonylurea with a chemical structure between that of traditional loop diuretics and Cl- channel blockers, used to treat hypertension.

Loperamide HCl is a selective μ-opioid receptor agonist opioid with Ki of 3.3 nM, 15-fold and 350-fold selective over the δ subtype and the κ subtype of the opioid receptor, used against diarrhea resulting from gastroenteritis or inflammatory bowel disease.
Dehydroacetic acid is an organic compound, used mostly as a fungicide and bactericide.
Atazanavir Sulfate is a HIV protease inhibitor with Ki of 2.66 nM in a cell-free assay.
Nicotinic Acid is a water-soluble vitamin belonging to the vitamin B family.
Nortriptyline Hydrochloride is the hydrochloride salt form of nortriptyline, a tricyclic antidepressant agent used for short-term treatment of various forms of depression.
Bosutinib (SKI-606) is a novel, dual Src/Abl inhibitor with IC50 of 1.2 nM and 1 nM in cell-free assays, respectively.
Dapagliflozin is a potent and selective hSGLT2 inhibitor with EC50 of 1.1 nM, exhibiting 1200-fold selectivity over hSGLT1. Phase 4.
Imatinib (STI571) is a multi-target inhibitor of tyrosine kinase with inhibition for v-Abl, c-Kit and PDGFR, IC50 values are 0.6 μM, 0.1 μM and 0.1 μM in cell-free or cell-based assays, respectively.
Valdecoxib is a potent and selective inhibitor of COX-2 with IC50 of 5 nM.
Simvastatin is a competitive inhibitor of HMG-CoA reductase with Ki of 0.1-0.2 nM in cell-free assays.
Kanamycin sulfate(Kanamycin monosulfate) is an aminoglycoside antibiotic, available in oral, intravenous, and intramuscular forms, and used to treat a wide variety of infections.

Oxaprozin is a non-narcotic, non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drug (NSAID) used to relieve the inflammation, swelling, stiffness, and joint pain associated with osteoarthritis and rheumatoid arthritis.
Piperonyl butoxide (PBO) is a man-made pesticide synergist, working with insect killers to increase their effectiveness.

Bafetinib (INNO-406) is a potent and selective dual Bcr-Abl/Lyn inhibitor with IC50 of 5.8 nM/19 nM in cell-free assays, does not inhibit the phosphorylation of the T315I mutant and is less potent to PDGFR and c-Kit. Phase 2.
Beclomethasone dipropionate  is a potent glucocorticoid steroid used for the treatment of rhinitis and sinusitis.
Oxyclozanide is a salicylanilide anthelmintic and mitochondrial uncoupling anthelmintic drug approved for veterinary use.
Hydroxyurea is an antineoplastic agent that inhibits DNA synthesis through the inhibition of ribonucleoside diphosphate reductase.
(-)-Tetramisole is an inhibitor of alkaline phosphatase, used as an anthelmintic.
Trazodone HCl is an antidepressant belonging to the class of serotonin receptor antagonists and reuptake inhibitors for treatment of anxiety disorders.
Tioconazole is an antifungal medication with an average IC50 of 1.7 μM.
Clorprenaline HCl is a β2-receptor agonist, it has a significant expansion of the bronchial effect.

Batimastat (BB-94) is a potent, broad spectrum matrix metalloprotease (MMP) inhibitor for MMP-1, MMP-2, MMP-9, MMP-7 and MMP-3 with IC50 of 3 nM, 4 nM, 4 nM, 6 nM and 20 nM, respectively. Also inhibits the activitity of other metalloproteases, such as ADAM17.

Osimertinib (AZD9291) is an oral, irreversible, and mutant-selective EGFR inhibitor with IC50 of 12.92, 11.44 and 493.8 nM for Exon 19 deletion EGFR, L858R/T790M EGFR, and WT EGFR in LoVo cells, respectively. Phase 3.
Famciclovir is a guanine analogue antiviral drug used for the treatment of various herpesvirus infections.
Brompheniramine hydrogen maleate is a histamine H1 receptors antagonist.
Saxagliptin is a selective and reversible DPP4 inhibitor with IC50 of 26 nM.
